bug.short_desc: Build fails with "this[setter[prop]] is not a function" in specific example

long_desc.thetext: The build application does not run in Firefox and ends with the following message: "this[setter[prop]] is not a function" if the optimization is completely disabled.
Created attachment 380 The sources for the test.

The issue was due to a typo of the property name "appearence" (rather than "appearance"). Changing the appearance name fixes the problem. This issue would have been reported in the source version if a logger had been enabled in the application code (The build version skips these tests).
Hint: Install logging in the "main" routine, like:
if (qx.core.Variant.isSet("qx.debug", "on")) // true by default in the source version { qx.log.appender.Native; qx.log.appender.Console; }
Hint: The use of gobal variables ("i", "page", "desktop") in the application code can easily lead to hard-to-track problems.
Hint: The application code also uses a non-existing appearance "hg-fenster"; there is also a warning about this in the source version if the logger is enabled.
